## Common Mistakes

### Wrong Code
```javascript
for (let i = 1; i <= 3; ) {
  console.log(i);
}
```
*Why this is incorrect:* Omitting the counter increment step causes loop conditions to remain True forever, creating an infinite loop that freezes memory.

### Correct Code
```javascript
for (let i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
  console.log(i);
}
```
*Why this is correct:* Validates statements cleanly.
